WEBVTT

00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:02.605
¡Bienvenido al tutorial final!

00:00:02.605 --> 00:00:05.413
Vamos a asegurarnos de que nunca te

00:00:05.413 --> 00:00:06.617
quedes sin disco.

00:00:06.617 --> 00:00:09.425
Vamos a expandir un repository completo en

00:00:09.425 --> 00:00:09.827
línea,

00:00:09.827 --> 00:00:12.234
devolver el espacio eliminado al pool,

00:00:12.234 --> 00:00:15.042
y luego enseñarle a la máquina a

00:00:15.042 --> 00:00:16.647
hacer ambas cosas automáticamente.

00:00:17.404 --> 00:00:19.339
Este es el modelo.

00:00:19.339 --> 00:00:22.241
Cada repository es un archivo en

00:00:22.241 --> 00:00:24.660
un pool de datastore compartido.

00:00:24.660 --> 00:00:27.563
Los repositories pueden crecer en línea

00:00:27.563 --> 00:00:29.981
mientras los containers siguen ejecutándose.

00:00:29.981 --> 00:00:32.884
Pero eliminar datos dentro de un

00:00:32.884 --> 00:00:35.786
repo no libera nada por sí

00:00:35.786 --> 00:00:36.270
solo.

00:00:36.270 --> 00:00:39.173
Trim es lo que devuelve los

00:00:39.173 --> 00:00:40.624
bloques al pool.

00:00:40.624 --> 00:00:43.526
Y una política automatiza ambas cosas.

00:00:46.803 --> 00:00:49.565
Fill the repository most of the way and

00:00:49.565 --> 00:00:49.910
check:

00:00:49.910 --> 00:00:51.636
the filesystem is getting tight.

00:00:57.577 --> 00:00:58.387
Casi lleno.

00:00:58.387 --> 00:01:00.007
Es hora de crecer.

00:01:03.291 --> 00:01:04.639
Grow it online.

00:01:04.639 --> 00:01:07.335
The encrypted container and the filesystem

00:01:07.335 --> 00:01:10.031
expand while the containers keep running

00:01:10.031 --> 00:01:11.379
— zero downtime,

00:01:11.379 --> 00:01:12.277
zero unmount.

00:01:15.277 --> 00:01:16.858
Cuatro gigabytes ahora.

00:01:16.858 --> 00:01:18.438
Nada se reinició.

00:01:21.748 --> 00:01:23.266
Verify from inside:

00:01:23.266 --> 00:01:24.279
same volume,

00:01:24.279 --> 00:01:25.797
double the room.

00:01:29.678 --> 00:01:31.793
La aplicación nunca lo notó.

00:01:35.077 --> 00:01:36.493
Now the other direction.

00:01:36.493 --> 00:01:38.972
Delete the big file — but watch:

00:01:38.972 --> 00:01:41.805
the pool does not get the space back

00:01:41.805 --> 00:01:42.159
yet.

00:01:42.159 --> 00:01:44.638
Deleted blocks stay reserved inside the image.

00:01:46.388 --> 00:01:48.362
Liberado dentro del repo,

00:01:48.362 --> 00:01:50.829
aún pertenece a la imagen.

00:01:54.128 --> 00:01:56.849
Trim hands those blocks back to the

00:01:56.849 --> 00:01:57.627
datastore pool,

00:01:57.627 --> 00:01:58.016
online.

00:01:58.016 --> 00:02:00.737
This is the step most setups forget.

00:02:03.737 --> 00:02:04.144
Recuperado.

00:02:04.144 --> 00:02:06.584
El pool puede respirar de nuevo.

00:02:09.895 --> 00:02:12.089
Now stop doing this by hand.

00:02:12.089 --> 00:02:14.649
The policy enables automatic growth up to

00:02:14.649 --> 00:02:16.112
a ceiling you choose,

00:02:16.112 --> 00:02:17.209
plus scheduled trims.

00:02:23.711 --> 00:02:24.537
Política guardada.

00:02:24.537 --> 00:02:27.426
La máquina se encarga a partir de

00:02:27.426 --> 00:02:27.839
aquí.

00:02:31.104 --> 00:02:32.201
Read it back:

00:02:32.201 --> 00:02:32.932
auto-grow on,

00:02:32.932 --> 00:02:34.395
ceiling at eight gigabytes,

00:02:34.395 --> 00:02:35.858
trim on a schedule.

00:02:40.241 --> 00:02:41.743
Configurado una vez,

00:02:41.743 --> 00:02:43.245
olvidado sin riesgos.

00:02:46.532 --> 00:02:49.087
And the view that ties it

00:02:49.087 --> 00:02:49.513
together:

00:02:49.513 --> 00:02:52.069
storage health shows every repo's usage,

00:02:52.069 --> 00:02:52.920
the pool,

00:02:52.920 --> 00:02:55.476
and how much copy-on-write sharing is

00:02:55.476 --> 00:02:56.328
saving you.

00:02:56.328 --> 00:02:57.275
Una vista:

00:02:57.275 --> 00:02:57.748
uso,

00:02:57.748 --> 00:03:00.115
ahorro y espacio para crecer.

00:03:00.883 --> 00:03:03.754
¡Y eso es todo en la serie!

00:03:03.754 --> 00:03:04.575
Dieciocho tutoriales,

00:03:04.575 --> 00:03:07.446
desde la instalación hasta el almacenamiento en

00:03:07.446 --> 00:03:08.267
piloto automático.

00:03:08.267 --> 00:03:10.728
Tus servidores son tuyos de nuevo.

00:03:10.728 --> 00:03:11.959
¡Gracias por ver!
